race.description: Peter Lewis Accountancy Services Mdn Hcp
race.comment: TYRONE'S POWER (2) resumes gelded and owns a Warwick Farm trial win. Brings strong metro and provincial form and McDougall is booked and is striking at 31% with the Litt yard. Looks ready to go and should be too good. MARGIN CALL (5) debuts for Ciaron Maher and is the unknown. He's been a while coming to the races but won a recent Randwick trial and that augurs well. Has an awkward barrier, but a bold run is likely. STEP QUICK (4) resumes and has switched to the Matt Kelley yard on a 92-day return. He's speedy and Owen will use the inside gate. Has pieces of form that would see him in the finish and expect him to be wound-up for the stable's race-day. Stablemate SOUK (1) resumes and has placed 8/10. Was backed off the map his last three and keep onside.
